**Super Micro Computer: A Rising Force in the Technology Sector**

In the latest Fortune 2024 ranking, Super Micro Computer has secured a notable position at number 498, marking a significant leap of 138 places from its previous ranking. This substantial gain is a testament to the company's impressive growth and resilience in the highly competitive technology sector.

Founded by Charles Liang, who still serves as the company's CEO, Super Micro Computer has demonstrated its ability to adapt and thrive in the ever-evolving technology landscape. As a leading manufacturer of computer hardware and server solutions, the company has managed to carve out a niche for itself in the Computers, Office Equipment industry.

One of the key factors contributing to Super Micro Computer's success is its commitment to innovation and job creation. The company has experienced a notable growth in jobs, which not only reflects its expanding operations but also its dedication to contributing to the economy. With a workforce of 5,126 employees, Super Micro Computer is an attractive employer in the industry.

In terms of financial performance, Super Micro Computer has delivered impressive results. The company's revenues have surged by 37.1% to $7,123.5 million, while its profits have skyrocketed by an impressive 124.4% to $640.0 million. These figures demonstrate the company's ability to drive growth and increase profitability, making it an attractive investment opportunity.

As of March 28, 2024, Super Micro Computer's market value stood at $59,137.7 million, with a minor update to $59,138.0 million. The company's assets have also grown to $3,674.7 million, providing a solid foundation for future expansion.

Headquartered in San Jose, California, Super Micro Computer operates as a public company, with its shares traded on the stock market under the ticker symbol SMCI. The company's website (https://www.supermicro.com) provides a comprehensive overview of its products and services, as well as its commitment to innovation and customer satisfaction.

While Super Micro Computer has not been recognized as one of the World's Most Admired Companies or one of the Best Companies to Work For, its recent ranking and financial performance suggest that it is a company to watch in the technology sector. As a newcomer to the Fortune 500, Super Micro Computer is poised to continue its upward trajectory, driven by its innovative spirit, commitment to job creation, and impressive financial growth.